DAY 282: George Washington Bridge with American Flag - for Columbus day - October 10, 2011.  This flag is renowned as the largest free flying American flag in the country and it is quite an awesome sight.  I've tried to get photos multiple times over the past year and a half but several times when I went to the bridge, the flag was not displayed as per the schedule.  Finally last June I did get some photos but it was a rainy day with a white sky and I've been wanting to get back.  So today, on the spur of the moment decided to try again. To see a few closeups of the flag, go to this link:  http://www.geoghanart.com/New-York-Skyline/George-Washington-Bridge/11317933_PFsxf4#1522810526_9MtRdMd
